        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 6:31AM EDT until June 22 at 6:45AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 631 AM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Windsor to near Starruca to near Peabrook, moving
south at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Rockland, Walton, Callicoon, Sanford, Susquehanna, Deposit,
Susquehanna Depot, Hancock, Fremont, and Windsor.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
